            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#k">Alexander Humboldt.</hi></head><lb break="yes"/>
                <p>&#x2014;Berlin papers received<lb break="yes"/>by the City of Baltimore contain the following<lb break="yes" />card from Alexander Humboldt:</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rendition="#et">&#x201C;<hi rendition="#k">Berlin,</hi> March 15, 1859.</hi>
                </dateline>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>&#x201C;Suffering beneath the pressure of a still increas-<lb break="no"/>ing correspondence, amounting to between sixteen<lb break="yes"/>hundred and two thousand communications per an-<lb break="no"/>num, and embracing letters, printed pamphlets on<lb break="yes"/>matters with which I am wholly unacquainted,<lb break="yes"/>manuscripts concerning which my opinion is desir-<lb break="no"/>ed, projects for emigrating and colonizing, the send-<lb break="no"/>ing of models, machines and natural curiosities, re-<lb break="no"/>quest of contributions to collections of autographs,<lb break="yes"/>offers to take charge of my domestic concerns, to<lb break="yes"/>cheer and enliven me, &#x0026;c., &#x0026;c., I must again pub-<lb break="no"/>licly urge all persons having my welfare at heart<lb break="yes"/>to exert their influence in my behalf, that indi-<lb break="no" />viduals in both continents may no longer busy<lb break="yes"/>themselves with my person and make of my house<lb break="yes"/>an intelligence office; and that I be allowed, in the<lb break="yes"/>declining state of my physical and mental powers,<lb break="yes"/>to enjoy some rest and leisure to attend to my du-<lb break="no"/>ties. May this cry for relief, which I utter with<lb break="yes"/>much reluctance and after reflection, not meet an<lb break="yes"/>unfriendly interpretation!</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <hi rendition="#et">&#x201C;<hi rendition="#k">Alexander Von Humboldt.</hi>&#x201D;</hi>
                    </salute>
                </closer>
            </div>
            <lb break="yes"/>
            <lb break="yes"/>
